//In the Scala REPL, compute the square root of 3, and then square that value.
//By how much does the result differ from 3? (Hint: The res variables are your
//friend.)
import scala.math._
sqrt(3)
sqrt(res1)

//Scala lets you multiply a string with a numberâ€”try out "crazy" * 3 in the REPL.
//What does this operation do? Where can you find it in Scaladoc?
"crazy" * 3 //crazycrazycrazy
"crazy".*(3) //longer form

//What does 10 max 2 mean? In which class is the max method defined?
// similar max(a,b) in java
//defined in RichInt
10 max 2
10.max(2)

//BigInt can be constructed using int,Using BigInt, compute 21024
BigInt(2) pow 1024
